STRICT.Definition: strongly limiting someone's freedom to behave as they wish, or likely to severely punish someone if they do not obey

INTRINSIC.Definition: being an extremely important and basic characteristic of a person or thing

PRODUCTIVE.Definition: causing or providing a good result or a large amount of something

PROFICIENTLY.Definition: in a way that shows skill and experience

VALUABLE.Definition: valuable information, advice, etc. is very helpful or important

POSSESS.Definition: to have or own something, or to have a particular quality

SOLELY.Definition: only and not involving anyone or anything else

IMMERSING.Definition: to become completely involved in something

COMPREHENSION.Definition: the ability to understand completely and be familiar with a situation, facts, etc.

KEY.Definition: very important and having a lot of influence on other people or things

LIKE-MINDED.Definition: people who are described as like-minded share the same opinions, ideas, or interests

UPBRINGING.Definition: the way in which you are treated and educated when young, especially by your parents, especially in relation to the effect that this has on how you behave and make moral decisions

MASTER.Definition: to learn how to do something well

HESITATE.Definition: to pause before you do or say something, often because you are uncertain or nervous about it

FORK.Definition: a place where a road, river, etc. divides into two parts, or either of those two parts

PASSIVE.Definition: not acting to influence or change a situation; allowing other people to be in control

BURNING DESIRE.Definition: a burning desire, need, etc., is one that is very strong

CONSISTENCY.Definition: the quality of always behaving or performing in a similar way, or of always happening in a similar way

ROLE MODELS.Definition: a person who someone admires and whose behavior they try to copy

DEDICATED.Definition: believing that something is very important and giving a lot of time and energy to it

NETWORK.Definition: people that you know, considered as a group whose members exchange information with each other
